# Compute Variables

The compute pillar estimates the energy required to generate each token.

| Variable | Units | Formula / Description |
|---|---|---|
| `chip_power_w` | W | Accelerator power draw from manufacturer specifications or inferred estimates |
| `chips_per_node` | chips | Number of accelerators assigned per compute node |
| `node_power_kw` | kW | `(chip_power_w × chips_per_node × 1.4) / 1000` |
| `throughput_tok_s` | tokens/sec | Model generation throughput benchmark |
| `node_energy_j_token` | J/token | `(node_power_kw × 1000) / throughput_tok_s` |

---

# Carbon Variables

The carbon pillar converts energy consumption into emissions based on regional electricity generation.

| Variable | Units | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `facility` | — | Serving data center location |
| `grid_region` | — | Assigned EPA eGRID region |
| `grid_lb_mwh` | lb CO₂e/MWh | Regional electricity emissions factor |
| `grid_ug_j` | μg CO₂e/J | Converted emissions intensity |

## Grid Conversion Formula

The conversion from pounds of CO₂e per MWh to micrograms of CO₂e per joule is:

\[
I_{grid}=\frac{lb/MWh \times 453.592}{3.6\times10^9}
\]

Where:

- `453.592` = grams per pound  
- `3.6 × 10⁹` = joules per MWh  

