# Cooling Variables

Cooling overhead is represented through Power Usage Effectiveness (PUE).

| Variable | Units | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `cooling_method` | — | Cooling classification (liquid, air, or unconfirmed) |
| `pue` | ratio | Assigned Power Usage Effectiveness value |
| `pue_source` | — | LBNL data category used for assignment |

---

# Final Metrics

These variables represent the final outputs used in the APEI framework.

| Variable | Units | Formula |
|---|---|---|
| `facility_energy_j_token` | J/token | `node_energy_j_token × pue` |
| `apei_gco2_token` | g CO₂e/token | `facility_energy_j_token × grid_gco2_j` |
| `query_carbon_500tok` | g CO₂e/query | `node_power × pue × grid × (TTFAT + 500/throughput)` |

